  "text": "The scan rate's effect on the electrochemical behavior of 2-CPE was investigated in 0.5 mol·L −1 NaOH solution ( Figure 6 ). At higher scan rates, the peak potentials changed gradually: the cathodic peak potentials shifted in a negative direction, and the homologous anodic peak potentials shifted in a positive direction. The inset of Figure 6 shows that the peak currents were proportional to the square root of the scan rates, suggesting that the redox processes for 2-CPE are surface-controlled [CITATION_1] . ",
